      "id": "2077807977193714080",
      "public_metrics": {
        "bookmark_count": 136,
        "impression_count": 265805,
        "like_count": 1017,
        "quote_count": 18,
        "reply_count": 152,
        "retweet_count": 71
      },
      "text": "In racing, tiny margins matter. AI can help teams find them.\n\nOpenAI\u2019s Joyce Ruffell and @RaceTekSystems co-founder @GarageGuyChase discuss with @AndrewMayne how racing teams use AI to turn track data into faster decisions\u2014from our research collaboration with Chip Ganassi Racing https://t.co/HC9FhV0I40"
    },
    {
      "author_id": "4398626122",
      "created_at": "2026-07-15T21:12:34.000Z",
      "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
        "2077501603050033634"
      ],
      "entities": {
        "urls": [
          {
            "display_url": "pic.x.com/hY3wkHVG7z",
            "end": 246,
            "expanded_url": "https://x.com/OpenAI/status/2077501603050033634/video/1",
            "media_key": "13_2077499668737781760",
            "start": 223,
            "url": "https://t.co/hY3wkHVG7z"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "2077501603050033634",
      "public_metrics": {
        "bookmark_count": 376,
        "impression_count": 336457,
        "like_count": 2011,
        "quote_count": 28,
        "reply_count": 196,
        "retweet_count": 129
      },
      "text": "A closer look at improved intelligence in GPT-Live: the model can keep a conversation going while helping with multiple tasks at once, like checking flights, pulling up local weather, and shaping an itinerary in real time. https://t.co/hY3wkHVG7z"
    },
    {
      "author_id": "4398626122",
      "created_at": "2026-07-15T17:34:30.000Z",
      "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
        "2077446723992228167"
      ],
      "id": "2077446723992228167",
      "public_metrics": {
        "bookmark_count": 30,
        "impression_count": 97998,
        "like_count": 388,
        "quote_count": 7,
        "reply_count": 20,
        "retweet_count": 11
      },
      "referenced_tweets": [
        {
          "id": "2077446722683650525",
          "type": "replied_to"
        }
      ],
      "text": "AI agents are already being used to improve the capabilities of our next-generation models.\n\nWe believe with GPT-Red that we have started to unlock a similar flywheel for safety, where today's models can be used to make tomorrow's models more robust, aligned, and trustworthy."
    },
    {
      "author_id": "4398626122",
      "created_at": "2026-07-15T17:34:30.000Z",
      "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
        "2077446722683650525"
      ],
      "id": "2077446722683650525",
      "public_metrics": {
        "bookmark_count": 28,
        "impression_count": 110512,
        "like_count": 398,
        "quote_count": 5,
        "reply_count": 15,
        "retweet_count": 15
      },
      "referenced_tweets": [
        {
          "id": "2077446721161093124",
          "type": "replied_to"
        }
      ],
      "text": "Training against GPT\u2011Red makes GPT\u20115.6 substantially more resilient. To measure this, we replayed some of GPT\u2011Red\u2019s strongest attacks\u2014none of which our models had seen during training. GPT\u20115.6 Sol proved to be our most robust model against prompt injections to date, with 6\u00d7 fewer"
    },
    {
      "author_id": "4398626122",
      "created_at": "2026-07-15T17:34:30.000Z",
      "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
        "2077446721161093124"
      ],
      "id": "2077446721161093124",
      "public_metrics": {
        "bookmark_count": 34,
        "impression_count": 79674,
        "like_count": 473,
        "quote_count": 7,
        "reply_count": 9,
        "retweet_count": 12
      },
      "referenced_tweets": [
        {
          "id": "2077446719990796505",
          "type": "replied_to"
        }
      ],
      "text": "GPT\u2011Red learns through adversarial self-play, where its goal is to prompt inject a variety of challenging defender models.\n\nEvery successful attack that GPT-Red finds is used to improve these defenders, pushing GPT\u2011Red to continuously find broader and more complex failures."
    },
    {
      "author_id": "4398626122",
      "created_at": "2026-07-15T17:34:29.000Z",
      "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
        "2077446719990796505"
      ],
      "id": "2077446719990796505",
      "public_metrics": {
        "bookmark_count": 27,
        "impression_count": 107287,
        "like_count": 586,
        "quote_count": 3,
        "reply_count": 14,
        "retweet_count": 16
      },
      "referenced_tweets": [
        {
          "id": "2077446718728425686",
          "type": "replied_to"
        }
      ],
      "text": "As model capabilities grow, safety and alignment must scale with them.\n\nRed-teaming is essential, but today\u2019s approaches are difficult to scale, creating a critical bottleneck.\n\nGPT\u2011Red is one way we\u2019re addressing it."
    },
    {
      "author_id": "4398626122",
      "created_at": "2026-07-15T17:34:29.000Z",
      "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
        "2077446718728425686"
      ],
